From nothing in Lucr. or Epicurus or any of their expositors, ancient or modern, have I been able to gather what their conception was, if they had one, of the superficial extent of an image5 whether for instance when you saw a thing of large extent, you saw it by a succession of single images, or of many images, advancing in parallel order and preserving their relative positions.
